			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Today i was in Plane of Valor when i finally managed to get my first 4 points of Leadership Advancement.
<br />

<br />
At first i thought to purchase mana enhancement, or Health regen. Then i decided to purchase the Delegate main Assist, it is fantastic and very useful, except for one scenerio, we have to be careful. Below is what happened...
<br />

<br />
We were at OC (Outer Cave) when our group rabbit went to pull.. Rabbit is delegated Main Assist.. now, rabbit pulled 2, so as usual rabbit tries to snare both and maintain aggro throughout.. but because rabbit is also main assist, the white circle under the 2 mobs kept switching. The whole party got rather confused as we threw spells and sent pets at the specially targetted mob to have the circle switched to another. In the end, i delegated myself as Main Assist and solved the problem.
<br />

<br />
Moral of the story, if you need to kite kill, don't make the rabbit as MA. Just  my word of caution to all who are new to this Leadership thingy.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
